## What is the purpose of the change

If client not commit or rollback transaction at the first time, will lead to proxy cannot end transaction in the future

For example
```java
Producer producer = provider.newProducerBuilder()
    .setTopics("test")
    .setTransactionChecker(messageView -> {
        // will lead to check for many times
        return TransactionResolution.COMMIT;
    })
    .setClientConfiguration(clientConfiguration)
    .build();
for (int i = 0; i < 1; i++) {
    Message message = provider.newMessageBuilder()
        .setTopic("test")
        .setBody("body".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))
        .build();
    Transaction transaction = producer.beginTransaction();
    producer.send(message, transaction);
    // not commit or rollback
}
```

So, use the last TransactionData saved in TransactionDataManager

